scriminative","kjv_def":"discerner","pos":"adjective","usage":"discerner(1x)"},"G2976":{"id":"G2976","lemma":"Λάζαρος","translit":"Lázaros","derivation":"probably of Hebrew origin (H0499);","strongs_def":"Lazarus (i.e. Elazar), the name of two Israelites (one imaginary)","kjv_def":"Lazarus","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Lazarus(11x)"},"G2918":{"id":"G2918","lemma":"κρίνον","translit":"krínon","derivation":"perhaps a prim word;","strongs_def":"a lily","kjv_def":"lily","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"lily(2x)"},"G2996":{"id":"G2996","lemma":"Λασαία","translit":"Lasaía","derivation":"of uncertain origin;","strongs_def":"Lasæa, a place in Crete","kjv_def":"Lasea"},"G2971":{"id":"G2971","lemma":"κώνωψ","translit":"kṓnōps","derivation":"apparently a derivative of the base of G2759 (κέντρον) and a derivative of G3700 (ὀπτάνομαι);","strongs_def":"a mosquito (from its stinging proboscis)","kjv_def":"gnat","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"gnat(1x)"},"G2997":{"id":"G2997","lemma":"λάσχω","translit":"láschō","derivation":"a strengthened form of a primary verb, which only occurs in this and another prolonged form as alternate in certain tenses;","strongs_def":"to crack open (from a fall)","kjv_def":"burst asunder","pos":"verb"},"G2974":{"id":"G2974","lemma":"κωφός","translit":"kōphós","derivation":"from G2875 (κόπτω);","strongs_def":"blunted, i.e. (figuratively) of hearing (deaf) or speech (dumb)","kjv_def":"deaf, dumb, speechless","pos":"adjective","usage":"dumb(8x), deaf(5x), speechless(1x)"},"G2905":{"id":"G2905","lemma":"κραυγάζω","translit":"kraugázō","derivation":"from G2906 (κραυγή);","strongs_def":"to clamor","kjv_def":"cry out","pos":"verb","usage":"cry(4x)"},"G2970":{"id":"G2970","lemma":"κῶμος","translit":"kōmos","derivation":"from G2749 (κεῖμαι);","strongs_def":"a carousal (as if letting loose)","kjv_def":"revelling, rioting","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"revelling(2x), rioting(1x)"},"G2975":{"id":"G2975","lemma":"λαγχάνω","translit":"lanchánō","derivation":"a prolonged form of a primary verb, which is only used as an alternate in certain tenses;","strongs_def":"to lot, i.e. determine (by implication, receive) especially by lot","kjv_def":"his lot be, cast lots, obtain","pos":"verb","usage":"obtain(2x)"},"G2940":{"id":"G2940","lemma":"κυβεία","translit":"kybeía","derivation":"from (a \"cube\", i.e. die for playing);","strongs_def":"gambling, i.e. (figuratively) artifice or fraud","kjv_def":"sleight","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"sleight(1x)"},"G2954":{"id":"G2954","lemma":"Κύπρος","translit":"Kýpros","derivation":"of uncertain origin;","strongs_def":"Cyprus, an island in the Mediterranean","kjv_def":"Cyprus","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Cyprus(5x)"},"G2901":{"id":"G2901","lemma":"κραταιόω","translit":"krataióō","derivation":"from G2900 (κραταιός);","strongs_def":"to empower, i.e. (passively) increase in vigor","kjv_def":"be strengthened, be (wax) strong","pos":"verb","usage":"strengthen(1x)"},"G2931":{"id":"G2931","lemma":"κρυφῆ","translit":"kryphē","derivation":"adverb from G2928 (κρύπτω);","strongs_def":"privately","kjv_def":"in secret","pos":"adverb"},"G2912":{"id":"G2912","lemma":"Κρής","translit":"Krḗs","derivation":"from G2914 (Κρήτη);","strongs_def":"a Cretan, i.e. inhabitant of Crete","kjv_def":"Crete, Cretian","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Cretians(2x), Cretes(1x)"},"G2973":{"id":"G2973","lemma":"Κωσάμ","translit":"Kōsám","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (compare H07081);","strongs_def":"Cosam (i.e. Kosam) an Israelite","kjv_def":"Cosam","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Cosam(1x)"},"G2937":{"id":"G2937","lemma":"κτίσις","translit":"ktísis","derivation":"from G2936 (κτίζω);","strongs_def":"original formation (properly, the act; by implication, the thing, literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"building, creation, creature, ordinance","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"creature(11x), creation(6x), building(1x), ordinance(1x)"}}